SIMPLE: closer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Closer
<hw>Clos"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, closes; specifically, a boot closer. See under
<er>Boot</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A finisher; that which finishes or
terminates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Masonry)</fld> <def>The last stone in a horizontal
course, if of a less size than the others, or a piece of brick finishing
a course.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Closereefed</ent>⟦br⟧
